Description: CVE-2026-57432 - fix SSize_t overflow when calculating structure size in pp_pack.c
 An integer overflow in S_measure_struct() in Perl's pack/unpack
 implementation lets a large repeat count on a fixed-length template item
 wrap the signed SSize_t running total negative. A subsequent position code
 (@, X, x) then passes a flawed signed bounds comparison, moving the buffer
 pointer out of bounds and leaking / reading heap memory past the input
 buffer. A template derived from untrusted input can therefore trigger an
 out-of-bounds heap read (CWE-190).
 .
 This patch folds two upstream commits:
  * 5f7eb6bbbe0510964e3fb1d6bb691e5445913e55 - detect the len*size and
    total+len*size overflow and croak with a new diagnostic (also adds the
    "Pack template structure size is too large" entry to perldiag.pod).
  * 40754edc72dd3e513d758153c0e2f0215897740e - avoid additional potential
    overflows in the 'B'/'b' and 'H'/'h' size rounding.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/Perl/perl5/commit/5f7eb6bbbe0510964e3fb1d6bb691e5445913e55
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/Perl/perl5/commit/40754edc72dd3e513d758153c0e2f0215897740e
Author: Paul "LeoNerd" Evans <leonerd@leonerd.org.uk>
Last-Update: 2026-07-15
---
--- a/pp_pack.c
+++ b/pp_pack.c
@@ -513,12 +513,12 @@
                 break;
             case 'B':
             case 'b':
-                len = (len + 7)/8;
+                len = (len / 8) + !!(len % 8);
                 size = 1;
                 break;
             case 'H':
             case 'h':
-                len = (len + 1)/2;
+                len = (len / 2) + !!(len % 2);
                 size = 1;
                 break;

@@ -528,6 +528,10 @@
                 break;
             }
         }
+        if ((size > 0) &&
+                ((len > SSize_t_MAX / size) ||         /* detect overflow of len * size */
+                 (len * size > SSize_t_MAX - total)))  /* detect overflow of total + len * size */
+            croak("Pack template structure size is too large");
         total += len * size;
     }
     return total;
--- a/pod/perldiag.pod
+++ b/pod/perldiag.pod
@@ -4995,6 +4995,12 @@
 (F) You can't specify a repeat count so large that it overflows your
 signed integers.  See L<perlfunc/pack>.

+=item Pack template structure size is too large
