Description: CVE-2026-8376 - Fix integer overflow in Perl_study_chunk leading to heap buffer overflow
 Perl_study_chunk in regcomp_study.c checked the size of the joined substring
 buffer in characters rather than bytes. For quantified fixed substrings with
 a large minimum count, (mincount * l) can overflow SSize_t, leading to an
 undersized SvGROW allocation and an out-of-bounds write. Add an overflow
 check before the copy and FAIL with "Regexp out of space" when overflow
 would occur.
