Description: CVE-2026-48959 - Fix integer comparison bug in IO::Uncompress::Unzip::fastForward
 The fastForward routine in IO::Uncompress::Unzip incorrectly compared and
 assigned length($offset) (the number of decimal digits in the offset)
 instead of $offset itself when deciding how many bytes to read on the final
 iteration. This caused the chunked smartReadExact loop to collapse from
 16 KiB reads to 1-19 byte reads when skipping past a large preceding entry
 in a non-Zip64 zip, leading to CPU exhaustion / denial of service. This is
 the root cause of CVE-2026-48959.
 .
 Fix by comparing and assigning $offset directly.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/pmqs/IO-Compress/commit/68db44076f4c1a86a2ffe53a958eac6cabaf72e2
Author: Paul Marquess <pmqs@cpan.org>
Last-Update: 2026-06-09
---
--- a/cpan/IO-Compress/lib/IO/Uncompress/Unzip.pm
+++ b/cpan/IO-Compress/lib/IO/Uncompress/Unzip.pm
@@ -157,8 +157,8 @@ sub fastForward
 
     while ($offset > 0)
     {
-        $c = length $offset
-            if length $offset < $c ;
+        $c = $offset
+            if $offset < $c ;
 
         $offset -= $c;
 
