Description: CVE-2026-48962 - Remove use of eval in File::GlobMapper
 IO::Compress before 2.220 ships File::GlobMapper, whose
 _parseOutputGlob() wrapped the caller-supplied output glob string in
 double quotes and stored it on the parser state. _getFiles() then
 evaluated that stored expression with eval STRING. A literal double
 quote in the output glob terminated the wrapping quotes, allowing
 trailing characters to be parsed as Perl code at the calling
 process's privilege (CWE-95, eval injection).
 .
 This patch replaces the eval-based output expansion with a safe
 regex-substitution scheme using non-printable delimiter and escape
 sentinels (BEGIN_DELIM/END_DELIM/HASH_ESC/STAR_ESC). Wildcards (*)
 and back-references (#1, #2, ...) are first rewritten to delimited
 placeholders during _parseOutputGlob, then substituted with the
 captured input pieces in _getFiles, and finally unescaped. No Perl
 code from the user-supplied glob is ever evaluated.
 .
 The accompanying t/globmapper.t additions cover delimiter and
 backslash escaping behaviour to lock the new logic in place.
